com.google.enterprise.adaptor.testing

Class RecordingResponse.AnchorMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.enterprise.adaptor.testing.RecordingResponse.AnchorMap
  • Enclosing class:
    RecordingResponse

    public static class RecordingResponse.AnchorMap
extends Object
    An unmodifiable view of the accumulated anchors as a multimap that supports duplicate, ordered key-value pairs. The anchor texts are the keys, and the anchor URIs are the values.

    This class is consistent with Guava's LinkedListMultimap, although it does not extend that class, or implement the ListMultimap interface or all of its methods.

      • entries

        public List<Map.Entry<String,URI>> entries()
        Gets an unmodifiable list of the anchors. The list is in insertion order, and may be empty, but will never be null. The keys (anchor texts) may be null. The values (anchor URIs) will not be null.
        Returns:
        an unmodifiable list of the accumulated anchors

      • keyList

        public List<String> keyList()

        Returns:
        a unmodifiable list of the accumulated anchor texts

      • keySet

        public Set<String> keySet()
        Gets an unmodifiable set of the unique anchor texts. The set is in insertion order based on the first appearance of each key, and may contain null.
        Returns:
        a unmodifiable set of the accumulated anchor texts

      • get

        public List<URI> get(String text)
        Gets an unmodifiable list of the accumulated anchor URIs that match the given text. The text may be null. The list is in insertion order, and may be empty, but will never be null. The URIs will not be null.
        Parameters:
        text - the anchor text to get the URIs for
        Returns:
        a unmodifiable list of the accumulated anchor URIs
